  "texts": [
    "In addition, to increase the diversity of the dataset and simulate realworld scenarios, random delays ranging from 0 to 1 ms and Doppler frequencies ranging from -4000 to 4000 Hz were introduced.",
    "The obtained I &Q samples were then used to compute the CAF maps over the Doppler-delay grid.",
    "These CAF maps can be viewed as images, where each pixel corresponds to a Doppler/delay cell, and the CAF value is denoted as Z i.",
    "However, processing such large CAF maps with a single NN model can be computationally expensive, as discussed earlier in the Section, Deep Neural Networks structure.",
    "For instance, when generating the CAF for a GPS L1 C/A signal with 50 Doppler bins (corresponding to 200 Hz bins for improved CAF peak identification), which are fed to a bank of parallel DNN binary classifiers to produce probability ratio maps."
  ],
